etails of this vessel in good faith but cannot guarantee or warrant the accuracy of this information nor warrant the condition of the vessel. A buyer should instruct his agents, or his surveyors, to investigate such details as the buyer desires validated. This vessel is offered subject to prior sale, price change, or withdrawal without notice.', 'The Company offers the details of this vessel in good faith but cannot guarantee or warrant the accuracy of this information nor warrant the condition of the vessel. A buyer should instruct his agents, or his surveyors, to investigate such details as the buyer desires validated. This vessel is offered subject to prior sale, price change, or withdrawal without notice.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Engine 1Engine Make:YamahaEngine Model:4-Stroke EFIEngine Year:2016Total Power:200hpEngine Hours:333Engine Type:OutboardDrive Type:Direct DriveFuel Type:GasPropeller Type:3 BladePropeller Material:Stainless SteelEngine 2Engine Make:YamahaEngine Model:4-Stroke EFIEngine Year:2016Total Power:200hpEngine Hours:333Engine Type:OutboardDrive Type:Jet DriveFuel Type:GasPropeller Type:3 BladePropeller Material:Stainless Steel', 'Yamaha', '4-Stroke EFI', '2016', '200hp', '333', 'Outboard', 'Direct Drive | Jet Drive', 'Gas', '3 Blade', 'Stainless Steel', 'Speed & DistanceCruising Speed:30.41knMax Speed:47.79knDimensionsLength Overall:28ftBeam:9.83ftMiscellaneousSeating Capacity:18Hull Material:HypalonTanksFresh Water Tank:Fuel Tank:140 gal Holding Tank:10 gal AccommodationsGuest Heads:1', '30.41kn', '47.79kn', NULL, '28ft', NULL, NULL, NULL, '9.83ft', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Hypalon', NULL, NULL, NULL, '140 gal', '10 gal', '1', '["https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/67/81/2015-zodiac-28-pro-optimum-power-9906781-20250826153507594-2.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1756248610000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/67/81/2015-zodiac-28-pro-optimum-power-9906781-20250811151152572-1.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1754951227000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/67/81/2015-zodiac-28-pro-optimum-power-9906781-20250826153506877-1.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1756248609000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/67/81/2015-zodiac-28-pro-optimum-power-9906781-20250811151249284-1.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1756247723000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/67/81/2015-zodiac-28-pro-optimum-power-9906781-20250811152015181-1.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1756247723000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/67/81/2015-zodiac-28-pro-optimum-power-9906781-20250811151534716-1.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1756247723000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/67/81/2015-zodiac-28-pro-optimum-power-9906781-20250811151857877-1.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1756247723000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/67/81/2015-zodiac-28-pro-optimum-power-9906781-20250811151811976-1.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1756247723000&exact&format=webp"]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Harwich, Massachusetts, US', 'Harwich', 'Massachusetts', 'US', 41.692615, -70.0698106, 'city', 'apple', 'matched', 'Harwich, Massachusetts, US', NULL, '2026-04-01T16:52:54.995Z', 1, 0);
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO boats (id, listing_id, source, url, make, model, year, length, price, currency, location, city, state, country, description, seller_type, listing_type, images, full_text, scraped_at, updated_at, search_length_min, search_length_max, search_type, search_location, contact_info, contact_name, contact_phone, other_details, disclaimer, features, electrical_equipment, electronics, inside_equipment, outside_equipment, additional_equipment, propulsion, engine_make, engine_model, engine_year_detail, total_power, engine_hours, engine_type_detail, drive_type, fuel_type_detail, propeller_type, propeller_material, specifications, cruising_speed, max_speed, range, length_overall, max_bridge_clearance, max_draft, min_draft_detail, beam_detail, dry_weight, windlass, electrical_circuit, deadrise_at_transom, hull_material, hull_shape, keel_type, fresh_water_tank, fuel_tank, holding_tank, guest_heads, source_images, entity_id, superseded_by_boat_id, dedupe_method, dedupe_confidence, normalized_location, normalized_city, normalized_state, normalized_country, geo_lat, geo_lng, geo_precision, geo_provider, geo_status, geo_query, geo_error, geo_updated_at, geo_normalization_version, needs_rescrape) VALUES (19972, '10110632', 'YachtWorld', 'https://www.yachtworld.com/yacht/1988-tartan-28-10110632/', 'Tartan', '28', 1988, '28ft', '26500', 'USD', 'Gloucester, Massachusetts', 'Gloucester', 'Massachusetts', 'US', 'Flying Cloud is a exceptional Performance/Cruiser, which offers a big-boat-feel, in 28 feet of boat. On any point of sail, you will never tire of her balanced design. With a high freeboard design...below deck is open and spacious, providing six feet of headroom throughout the main salon. (7) opening ports and (2) opening hatches allow for great ventilation and lots of light. The V-berth is comfortable for a couple, and the quarter berth is also spacious...if needed, there is a slide-out settee double berth in the main salon. The interior teak woodwork is clean and rich with hand rubbed oil, along with the classic teak and holly cabin sole. The galley and head have pressurized water, and the galley sink also has a foot pump. The icebox is deep and well insulated...with a teak grating shelf and separate drainage. The Gimbaled Stove is CNG with two top burners. Access to the engine is excellent for standard maintenance, and there is an engine pan to prevent fluids from leaking into the bilge. The bilge is very clean, no smells. Flying Cloud is a pleasure to sail…her fin keel with spade rudder lets her turn on a dime. She is easy to set into a groove, on any point of sail. The reverse transom also helps to keep her stable when running downwind…New Garmin Chartplotter and Radar installed 2025, other electronics include; Depth, Temp and Speed, Autopilot, VHF, plus solar panels....batteries new 2025. Routine maintenance on the 18 hp Yanmar diesel performed every season. ''Flying Cloud'' edged out some top local racers, in last year''s Cape Ann Challenge, as the Overall Winner....she is a wonderful boat inside and out…and a lot of fun to sail.', 'dealer', 'sale', '["https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/6/32/1988-tartan-28-sail-10110632-20260316082442615-1.jpg?w=1920&h=267&t=1773675591000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/6/32/1988-tartan-28-sail-10110632-20260316082443375-2.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1773675587000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/6/32/1988-tartan-28-sail-10110632-20260316082821769-1.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1773675806000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/6/32/1988-tartan-28-sail-10110632-20260316082820162-2.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1773675803000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/6/32/1988-tartan-28-sail-10110632-20260316082820767-3.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1773675814000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/6/32/1988-tartan-28-sail-10110632-20260316083244776-1.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1773676246000&exact=&format=webp"]', 'Boat DetailsDescriptionFlying Cloud is a exceptional Performance/Cruiser, which offers a big-boat-feel, in 28 feet of boat. On any point of sail, you will never tire of her balanced design. With a high freeboard design...below deck is open and spacious, providing six feet of headroom throughout the main salon. (7) opening ports and (2) opening hatches allow for great ventilation and lots of light. The V-berth is comfortable for a couple, and the quarter berth is also spacious...if needed, there is a slide-out settee double berth in the main salon. The interior teak woodwork is clean and rich with hand rubbed oil, along with the classic teak and holly cabin sole. The galley and head have pressurized water, and the galley sink also has a foot pump. The icebox is deep and well insulated...with a teak grating shelf and separate drainage. The Gimbaled Stove is CNG with two top burners. Access to the engine is excellent for standard maintenance, and there is an engine pan to prevent fluids from leaking into the bilge. The bilge is very clean, no smells. Flying Cloud is a pleasure to sail…her fin keel with spade rudder lets her turn on a dime. She is easy to set into a groove, on any point of sail. The reverse transom also helps to keep her stable when running downwind…New Garmin Chartplotter and Radar installed 2025, other electronics include; Depth, Temp and Speed, Autopilot, VHF, plus solar panels....batteries new 2025. Routine maintenance on the 18 hp Yanmar diesel performed every season. ''Flying Cloud'' edged out some top local racers, in last year''s Cape Ann Challenge, as the Overall Winner....she is a wonderful boat inside and out…and a lot of fun to sail. Show MoreContact InformationPlease contact Paul Chasse at 781-631-4910Other DetailsAccommodationsFlying Cloud featur…', '2026-04-01T04:07:16.929Z', '2026-04-01T04:07:16.929Z', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Please contact Paul Chasse at 781-631-4910', 'Paul Chasse', '781-631-4910', 'AccommodationsFlying Cloud features a beautiful oiled teak interior with a varnished teak & holy sole, There are accommodations for up to six with 2 in the forward cabin, 3 in the main cabin and 1 in the quarterberth. The woodwork is in excellent condition and shows very well. The interior overall is very clean and dry with no evidence of leaks or mildew. There are 9 opening ports and one hatch forward that let in plenty of light and air. Starting forward, The Forward Cabin features a double V-berth with filler. Storage under. There is a large hanging locker aft to port. The head is aft the starboard. The head features a manual toilet with holding tank and deck pumpout, vanity & Sink with pull-out shower, and plenty of storage. Heading aft is the main cabin with a small settee to port, storage outboard and under, and access to the main switch panel and stereo.The starboard settee converts to a double. There are nice teak storage lockers outboard of settee. The drop down teak dining table folds out to accommodate both settees. There are 6 opening ports in the main cabin. The U-Shaped galley is aft to port and a single quarterberth is aft to starboard.GalleyU-shaped galley Located af…', 'The Company offers the details of this vessel in good faith but cannot guarantee or warrant the accuracy of this information nor warrant the condition of the vessel. A buyer should instruct his agents, or his surveyors, to investigate such details as the buyer desires validated. This vessel is offered subject to prior sale, price change, or withdrawal without notice.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Engine Make:YanmarEngine Model:2GM20FEngine Year:1988Total Power:16hpEngine Type:InboardDrive Type:Direct DriveFuel Type:DieselPropeller Type:3 Blade', 'Yanmar', '2GM20F', '1988', '16hp', NULL, 'Inboard', 'Direct Drive', 'Diesel', '3 Blade', NULL, 'Speed & DistanceCruising Speed:5.5knDimensionsLength Overall:28.25ftMax Draft:4.92ftBeam:9.83ftLength at Waterline:23.25ftMiscellaneousHull Material:FiberglassKeel Type:Fin KeelTanksFresh Water Tank:1 x 30 gal Fuel Tank:1 x 18 gal Holding Tank:', '5.5kn', NULL, NULL, '28.25ft', NULL, '4.92ft', NULL, '9.83ftLength at Waterline:23.25ft', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Fiberglass', NULL, 'Fin Keel', '1 x 30 gal', '1 x 18 gal', NULL, NULL, '["https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/6/32/1988-tartan-28-sail-10110632-20260316082442615-1.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1773675591000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/6/32/1988-tartan-28-sail-10110632-20260316082443375-2.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1773675587000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/6/32/1988-tartan-28-sail-10110632-20260316082821769-1.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1773675806000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/6/32/1988-tartan-28-sail-10110632-20260316082820162-2.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1773675803000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/97/89/5099789_20150526183126510_1_XLARGE.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1773675291000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/97/89/5099789_20150526183130653_1_XLARGE.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1773675291000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/97/89/5099789_20150526184746255_1_XLARGE.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1773675291000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/97/89/5099789_20150526183318287_1_XLARGE.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1773675291000&exact&format=webp"]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Gloucester, Massachusetts, US', 'Gloucester', 'Massachusetts', 'US', 42.6140542, -70.6631595, 'city', 'apple', 'matched', 'Gloucester, Massachusetts, US', NULL, '2026-04-01T04:07:16.929Z', 1, 0);
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO boats (id, listing_id, source, url, make, model, year, length, price, currency, location, city, state, country, description, seller_type, listing_type, images, full_text, scraped_at, updated_at, search_length_min, search_length_max, search_type, search_location, contact_info, contact_name, contact_phone, other_details, disclaimer, features, electrical_equipment, electronics, inside_equipment, outside_equipment, additional_equipment, propulsion, engine_make, engine_model, engine_year_detail, total_power, engine_hours, engine_type_detail, drive_type, fuel_type_detail, propeller_type, propeller_material, specifications, cruising_speed, max_speed, range, length_overall, max_bridge_clearance, max_draft, min_draft_detail, beam_detail, dry_weight, windlass, electrical_circuit, deadrise_at_transom, hull_material, hull_shape, keel_type, fresh_water_tank, fuel_tank, holding_tank, guest_heads, source_images, entity_id, superseded_by_boat_id, dedupe_method, dedupe_confidence, normalized_location, normalized_city, normalized_state, normalized_country, geo_lat, geo_lng, geo_precision, geo_provider, geo_status, geo_query, geo_error, geo_updated_at, geo_normalization_version, needs_rescrape) VALUES (19932, '10116321', 'YachtWorld', 'https://www.yachtworld.com/yacht/2013-j-boats-j-70-10116321/', 'J', 'Boats J/70', 2013, '23ft', '60000', 'USD', 'Marblehead, Massachusetts', 'Marblehead', 'Massachusetts', 'US', 'The J/70 Speedster (22.75 feet) is J/Boats'' first ramp-launchable, keelboat - designed to fulfill the need for an easy-to-own, high performance one-design that''s exciting to sail, stable enough for the entire family, AND easy to tow, rig, launch and sail. Since its introduction in 2012, the J/70 has become the most prolific sportboat in the world with 1800+ boats sailing in 30+ countries. It all started with a boat that''s a BLAST to sail! "Bad Hombres". Hull #339 built in 2013 is a proven winner, beautifully maintained and comes with many upgrades which include: Complete bottom/appendages faired by Chris Small (2019) 2018 Triad Trailer with preferred "bunk" supports, brakes, spare tire 2 Fiberglass trailer boxes All Doyle sail inventory (see "sails" description). 2.3 HP Outboard Engine Covers (see "covers" description) Raymarine wireless Micronet Race Master (solar) w/ through-hull paddle wheel and Velocitek Southern Spars mast and boom Keel crane (never used) JCD Carbon tiller extension Harken Dock Pads Cockpit line bag/water bottle storage Retractable companionway spinnaker bag Upgraded running rigging (Sail22) All class required gear Lifting straps Class measurement Cert. (Manufacturer''s Declaration) Podium Race Results: 2025 Corinthian Worlds 6th place 2025 Ted Hood Regatta 1st place 2025 New England Championship 2nd place corinthian 2024 New England Championship 1st place corinthian 2022 New England Championship 1st place corinthian 2022 North American Championship 1st place corinthian 2021 New England Championship 1st place corinthian 2019 North American Championship 3rd place corinthian', 'dealer', 'sale', '["https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/63/21/2013-j-boats-j70-sail-10116321-20260317124054754-1.jpg?w=1920&h=267&t=1773777496000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/63/21/2013-j-boats-j70-sail-10116321-20260317140012114-1.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1773782114000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/63/21/2013-j-boats-j70-sail-10116321-20260317123042575-1.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1773781257000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/63/21/2013-j-boats-j70-sail-10116321-20260317123042729-2.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1773781257000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/63/21/2013-j-boats-j70-sail-10116321-20260317123042892-3.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1773781257000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/63/21/2013-j-boats-j70-sail-10116321-20260317123043031-4.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1773781257000&exact=&format=webp"]', 'Boat DetailsDescriptionThe J/70 Speedster (22.75 feet) is J/Boats'' first ramp-launchable, keelboat - designed to fulfill the need for an easy-to-own, high performance one-design that''s exciting to sail, stable enough for the entire family, AND easy to tow, rig, launch and sail. Since its introduction in 2012, the J/70 has become the most prolific sportboat in the world with 1800+ boats sailing in 30+ countries. It all started with a boat that''s a BLAST to sail! "Bad Hombres". Hull #339 built in 2013 is a proven winner, beautifully maintained and comes with many upgrades which include: Complete bottom/appendages faired by Chris Small (2019) 2018 Triad Trailer with preferred "bunk" supports, brakes, spare tire 2 Fiberglass trailer boxes All Doyle sail inventory (see "sails" description). 2.3 HP Outboard Engine Covers (see "covers" description) Raymarine wireless Micronet Race Master (solar) w/ through-hull paddle wheel and Velocitek Southern Spars mast and boom Keel crane (never used) JCD Carbon tiller extension Harken Dock Pads Cockpit line bag/water bottle storage Retractable companionway spinnaker bag Upgraded running rigging (Sail22) All class required gear Lifting straps Class measurement Cert. (Manufacturer''s Declaration) Podium Race Results: 2025 Corinthian Worlds 6th place 2025 Ted Hood Regatta 1st place 2025 New England Championship 2nd place corinthian 2024 New England Championship 1st place corinthian 2022 New England Championship 1st place corinthian 2022 North American Championship 1st place corinthian 2021 New England Championship 1st place corinthian 2019 North American Championship 3rd place corinthian Show MoreContact InformationPlease contact Bruce Durkee at 508-367-5056Other DetailsDisclaimerThe Company offers the details of this vessel in good faith bu…', '2026-04-01T04:03:03.245Z', '2026-04-01T04:03:03.245Z', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Please contact Bruce Durkee at 508-367-5056', 'Bruce Durkee', '508-367-5056', 'Di