85000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_050420220116_2.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930188000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_161020210116_3.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930189000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_161020210117_4.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930187000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_050420220116_5.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930186000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_050420220116_6.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930186000&exact&format=webp"]', 'Boat DetailsDescriptionTop of the range is an understatement when it comes to describing the MC100. This magnificent 100-foot catamaran takes the McConaghy Multihull series into superyacht territory with superlative style and eco-efficiency. Following the proven concept of the MC line of multihulls, the MC100 retains that ability to truly sail the yacht when at sea, whilst also offering exquisite comfort, luxury and space within the social areas.. The MC100 is World class..Other DetailsInventoryELECTRICAL SYSTEMS McConaghy will complete the full electrical design. McConaghy will supply the main switchboards and monitoring equipment as well as the PLC based monitoring and control systems. McConaghy will supervise the electrical install and complete all electrical commissioning on the vessel. 1401 AC Power ? 1 x Generator ? 1 x Shore inlet up to 63 Amp ? 1 x Galvanic Isolator ( Isolation transformers can be added if prefered) ? 3 x Mass Combi Pro 24/3500 Inverter Chargers ( Total output continuous 10,500 watt ) ? 1 x ACMI Main switchboard to handle all AC mains and provide transfer by auto and manual functions. ? 4 x ACOI AC subboards to provide AC circuit control and monitoring to sub circuits ? Relevant protections 1402 DC Power ? 8 x Mastervolt MLI 24/5500 Lithium batteries ( house ) ? 1 x Mastervolt MLI 24/5500 Lithium batteries ( Radio / Emergency battery ) ? DC/DC Converters for network and navigation equipments ? Remote Battery switch control of house and start batteries ? 3 x Mass Combi Pro 24/3500 Inverter Chargers ( Total 300 Amps charge at 24V ) ? 2 x Delstar / Bermantec 240Amp house alternators with Mastervolt Alpha Pro III regulators ? Battery chargers for start batteries ? Emergency parallel between engine start systems ? Custom bus bars for main positive an…', '2026-04-01T01:20:52.844Z', '2026-04-01T01:20:52.844Z', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'InventoryELECTRICAL SYSTEMS McConaghy will complete the full electrical design. McConaghy will supply the main switchboards and monitoring equipment as well as the PLC based monitoring and control systems. McConaghy will supervise the electrical install and complete all electrical commissioning on the vessel. 1401 AC Power ? 1 x Generator ? 1 x Shore inlet up to 63 Amp ? 1 x Galvanic Isolator ( Isolation transformers can be added if prefered) ? 3 x Mass Combi Pro 24/3500 Inverter Chargers ( Total output continuous 10,500 watt ) ? 1 x ACMI Main switchboard to handle all AC mains and provide transfer by auto and manual functions. ? 4 x ACOI AC subboards to provide AC circuit control and monitoring to sub circuits ? Relevant protections 1402 DC Power ? 8 x Mastervolt MLI 24/5500 Lithium batteries ( house ) ? 1 x Mastervolt MLI 24/5500 Lithium batteries ( Radio / Emergency battery ) ? DC/DC Converters for network and navigation equipments ? Remote Battery switch control of house and start batteries ? 3 x Mass Combi Pro 24/3500 Inverter Chargers ( Total 300 Amps charge at 24V ) ? 2 x Delstar / Bermantec 240Amp house alternators with Mastervolt Alpha Pro III regulators ? Battery chargers…', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Engine 1Engine Type:InboardDrive Type:Direct DriveFuel Type:DieselEngine 2Engine Type:InboardFuel Type:Diesel', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Inboard', 'Direct Drive', 'Diesel', NULL, NULL, 'DimensionsLength Overall:100ftMax Draft:7.22ftBeam:40.35ftMiscellaneousHull Material:OtherKeel Type:OtherTanksFresh Water Tank:Fuel Tank:Holding Tank:AccommodationsGuest Cabins:5', NULL, NULL, NULL, '100ft', NULL, '7.22ft', NULL, '40.35ft', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Other', NULL, 'Other', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '["https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_161020210115_1.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930185000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_050420220116_2.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930188000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_161020210116_3.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930189000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_161020210117_4.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930187000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_050420220116_5.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930186000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_050420220116_6.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930186000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_050420220116_7.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930188000&exact&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/14/84/8071484_0_050420220116_8.jpg?w=1028&ratio=default&t=1774930189000&exact&format=webp"]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Factory, China, US', 'Factory', 'China', 'US', NULL, NULL, 'city', 'apple', 'failed', 'Factory, China, US', 'Apple Maps token exchange failed (401): {"error":{"message":"Not Authorized","details":[]}}', '2026-04-01T01:20:52.844Z', 1, 0);
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO boats (id, listing_id, source, url, make, model, year, length, price, currency, location, city, state, country, description, seller_type, listing_type, images, full_text, scraped_at, updated_at, search_length_min, search_length_max, search_type, search_location, contact_info, contact_name, contact_phone, other_details, disclaimer, features, electrical_equipment, electronics, inside_equipment, outside_equipment, additional_equipment, propulsion, engine_make, engine_model, engine_year_detail, total_power, engine_hours, engine_type_detail, drive_type, fuel_type_detail, propeller_type, propeller_material, specifications, cruising_speed, max_speed, range, length_overall, max_bridge_clearance, max_draft, min_draft_detail, beam_detail, dry_weight, windlass, electrical_circuit, deadrise_at_transom, hull_material, hull_shape, keel_type, fresh_water_tank, fuel_tank, holding_tank, guest_heads, source_images, entity_id, superseded_by_boat_id, dedupe_method, dedupe_confidence, normalized_location, normalized_city, normalized_state, normalized_country, geo_lat, geo_lng, geo_precision, geo_provider, geo_status, geo_query, geo_error, geo_updated_at, geo_normalization_version, needs_rescrape) VALUES (20640, '9974845', 'YachtWorld', 'https://www.yachtworld.com/yacht/1964-benetti-tugboat-9974845/', 'Benetti', 'tugboat', 1964, '96ft', '22000000', 'EUR', 'La Spezia, La Spezia', 'La Spezia', 'La Spezia', 'US', 'San Gennaro – From Tugboat to Timeless Yacht San Gennaro is a magnificent 29-metre Benetti tugboat, originally launched in 1964 and later transformed from a hardworking vessel into a distinguished private yacht. The ambitious refit project, carried out by Lenci Marine, involved a complete renewal of the superstructures. These were expanded to create elegant living spaces — a spacious salon, a dining room, and a fully equipped galley. On the upper deck, a grand wheelhouse and the owner’s suite were added, while the lower deck was redesigned to include three guest cabins and a laundry area. The crew quarters, consisting of two twin cabins, are located aft of the engine room. Every detail reflects timeless craftsmanship: the interiors are finished in fine teak wood, harmoniously matched with teak decking across all three levels, creating a warm and classic maritime atmosphere. The conversion was a true labor of restoration and respect for tradition. The engine room underwent a complete overhaul, allowing the yacht to preserve its original MAN engine, delivering 1,051 horsepower at 360 rpm. The refit was carried out at the Ortona Navi shipyard on the Adriatic coast, and San Gennaro was proudly re-launched for the 2005 season, ready to sail once again — this time as a symbol of nautical elegance and history reborn.', 'dealer', 'sale', '["https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/48/45/1964-benetti-tugboat-power-9974845-20251010041258310-1.jpg?w=1920&h=267&t=1760095681000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/48/45/1964-benetti-tugboat-power-9974845-20251010041259467-2.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1760095682000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/48/45/1964-benetti-tugboat-power-9974845-20251010041300502-3.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1760095683000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/48/45/1964-benetti-tugboat-power-9974845-20251010041301603-4.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1760095685000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/48/45/1964-benetti-tugboat-power-9974845-20251010041303879-1.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1760095686000&exact=&format=webp","https://images.boatsgroup.com/resize/1/48/45/1964-benetti-tugboat-power-9974845-20251010041304507-2.jpg?w=1920&ratio=default&t=1760095685000&exact=&format=webp"]', 'Boat DetailsDescriptionSan Gennaro – From Tugboat to Timeless Yacht San Gennaro is a magnificent 29-metre Benetti tugboat, originally launched in 1964 and later transformed from a hardworking vessel into a distinguished private yacht. The ambitious refit project, carried out by Lenci Marine, involved a complete renewal of the superstructures. These were expanded to create elegant living spaces — a spacious salon, a dining room, and a fully equipped galley. On the upper deck, a grand wheelhouse and the owner’s suite were added, while the lower deck was redesigned to include three guest cabins and a laundry area. The crew quarters, consisting of two twin cabins, are located aft of the engine room. Every detail reflects timeless craftsmanship: the interiors are finished in fine teak wood, harmoniously matched with teak decking across all three levels, creating a warm and classic maritime atmosphere. The conversion was a true labor of restoration and respect for tradition. The engine room underwent a complete overhaul, allowing the yacht to preserve its original MAN engine, delivering 1,051 horsepower at 360 rpm. The refit was carried out at the Ortona Navi shipyard on the Adriatic coast, and San Gennaro was proudly re-launched for the 2005 season, ready to sail once again — this time as a symbol of nautical elegance and history reborn. Show MoreContact InformationPlease contact Karin Paggi at +39 347 9109201Other DetailsDisclaimerBenetti 29 Tugboat – M/Y San Gennaro Year: 1964 | Length: 29 m | Hull: Black | Superstructure: Military Green A timeless expression of classic Italian shipbuilding, the San Gennaro is a beautifully refitted 29-meter Benetti tugboat that blends authentic maritime heritage with modern luxury. Originally launched in 1964, this extraordinary vessel no…', '2026-04-01T17:00:33.344Z', '2026-04-01T17:00:33.344Z', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Please contact Karin Paggi at +39 347 9109201', 'Karin Paggi', '347 9109201', 'DisclaimerBenetti 29 Tugboat – M/Y San Gennaro Year: 1964 | Length: 29 m | Hull: Black | Superstructure: Military Green A timeless expression of classic Italian shipbuilding, the San Gennaro is a beautifully refitted 29-meter Benetti tugboat that blends authentic maritime heritage with modern luxury. Originally launched in 1964, this extraordinary vessel now combines the strength of her origins with the comfort and sophistication of a contemporary motor yacht. Exterior & Design Featuring a striking black hull and military green superstructure, San Gennaro stands out with her powerful presence and vintage charm. The decks are finished in teak and sinteak, providing warmth, durability, and timeless elegance. The yacht offers multiple outdoor relaxation areas, including rear and flybridge sundecks with bimini-top shade, perfect for lounging or entertaining at sea. Accommodation & Interior Inside, San Gennaro offers a spacious and beautifully appointed layout with four cabins and four bathrooms, each with shower cubicle, bidet, and electric toilet. The owner’s suite features a TV and safe, while the saloon includes a retractable television and Hi-Fi sound system with external speakers.…', 'Benetti 29 Tugboat – M/Y San Gennaro Year: 1964 | Length: 29 m | Hull: Black | Superstructure: Military Green A timeless expression of classic Italian shipbuilding, the San Gennaro is a beautifully refitted 29-meter Benetti tugboat that blends authentic maritime heritage with modern luxury. Originally launched in 1964, this extraordinary vessel now combines the strength of her origins with the comfort and sophistication of a contemporary motor yacht. Exterior & Design Featuring a striking black hull and military green superstructure, San Gennaro stands out with her powerful presence and vintage charm. The decks are finished in teak and sinteak, providing warmth, durability, and timeless elegance. The yacht offers multiple outdoor relaxation areas, including rear and flybridge sundecks with…', 'Electrical EquipmentShore Power Inlet:✓Generator:✓ElectronicsDepthsounder:✓Radar:✓Log-Speedometer:✓Radar Detector:✓Wind Speed and Direction:✓Repeater(s):✓TV Set:✓Plotter:✓Radio:✓Compass:✓CD Player:✓GPS:✓VHF:✓Flat Screen TV:✓Inside EquipmentBow Thruster:✓Washing Machin